The paper discusses mathematical modeling and analysis of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also specifically mentions applications from the robotics domain, which suggests that it could also be categorized under Robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of individual agents and how it contributes to the collective behavior of the system, which is a topic that falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the dynamics of the system, which could be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the probabilistic description of the collective behavior, which could be categorized under Signal Processing (cs.SI).
